#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.238"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.238:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.238:0.2"
msgid "24. Kammavagga"
msgstr "24. Deeds"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.238:0.3"
msgid "238. Bojjhaṅgasutta"
msgstr "238. Awakening Factors"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.238:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, kammāni … pe … kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ … pe … idha, "
"bhikkhave, ekacco sabyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti … pe … idaṃ "
"vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhaṃ kaṇhavipākaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I declare these four kinds of deeds, having realized them with "
"my own insight. ... And what are dark deeds with dark results? It’s when "
"someone makes hurtful choices by way of body, speech, and mind. These are "
"called dark deeds with dark results."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.238:2.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ?"
msgstr "And what are bright deeds with bright results?"

msgctxt "an4.238:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco abyābajjhaṃ kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti … pe … idaṃ "
"vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ sukkaṃ sukkavipākaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone makes pleasing choices by way of body, speech, and mind. "
"These are called bright deeds with bright results."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.237"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.238:3.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ?"
msgstr "And what are dark and bright deeds with dark and bright results?"

msgctxt "an4.238:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco sabyābajjhampi abyābajjhampi kāyasaṅkhāraṃ "
"abhisaṅkharoti … pe … idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ kaṇhasukkaṃ "
"kaṇhasukkavipākaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone makes both hurtful and pleasing choices by way of body, "
"speech, and mind. These are called dark and bright deeds with dark and "
"bright results."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.238:4.1"
msgid ""
"Katamañca, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ kammakkhayāya "
"saṃvattati?"
msgstr ""
"And what are neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright "
"results, which lead to the ending of deeds?"

msgctxt "an4.238:4.2"
msgid ""
"Satisambojjhaṅgo, dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo, vīriyasambojjhaṅgo, "
"pītisambojjhaṅgo, passaddhisambojjhaṅgo, samādhisambojjhaṅgo, "
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo—"
msgstr ""
"The awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, "
"rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity."

msgctxt "an4.238:4.3"
msgid ""
"idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kammaṃ akaṇhaasukkaṃ akaṇhaasukkavipākaṃ "
"kammakkhayāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"These are called neither dark nor bright deeds with neither dark nor bright "
"results, which lead to the ending of deeds."

msgctxt "an4.238:4.4"
msgid ""
"Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri kammāni mayā sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"paveditānī”ti."
msgstr ""
"These are the four kinds of deeds that I declare, having realized them with "
"my own insight.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.238:4.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
